and anything which falls outside them is utterly forbidden and may carry a befitting punishment
(detailed on section 2). The use of any of the software implies that you aknowledge and agree 
throroughly to the following terms.

Section 1; access & reproduction terms:

1. Any of the software may be accessed at any time by any free individual or organization.
2. Any of the software may be reproduced only as long as there exist a clear copyright mention
   on any visible part of the program wich uses the reproduction.
  2.1 In case there exists any modification of the original program, it's considered as reproduction.
3. If any of the following software were to be reproduced for commercial purposes,
   its creator may ask for a compensation, which must be accorded beforehand with him.
4. The software is free of any warranty or whatsoever, and all responsability befalls on the user
   and the creator shall be discharged of any actions taken with the software.
5. For educative purposes, there is no license needed, althought the creator must be informed beforehand.
  5.1 If the program license isn't free, it's considered as commercial use regardless of how is the program classified.

Section 2; punishments:

1. If the user fails to follow the points 1.2 or 1.3 of the license, 
   his or her software may be asked to be removed from whichever media it's beign spread throught (Steam, Play Store,...), 
   and a proper lawsuit may be issued in case of commercial use. 
2. If the user fails to follow the point 1.4 of the license, the user shall not make any complain to the creator,
   and all attempts to make any claim shall be taken as proof of further responsability of the user
   in any problem he or she has come throught.
3. If the user fails to follow the point 1.5 of the license, the software may be removed in whichever media 
   it's beign spread throught until a proper apology to the creator is made.
   
Section 3; contact:

1. In order to follow any point of this license which requires an agreement with the creator,
   the following email must be used: elgurudelasnecropolis@gmail.com. Also, the email must be written in a formal way
   and the topic of it shall be clearly disclosed
   
